# Build from blueprint (no patches)

One building, one plan, many trades. **Do not paint a room before plumbing is roughed in.**

## Before writing code

1. **Intention** — Ultimate goal in one line (V1 sacred metric: **first booking**). What “done” means for the owner/guest, not for the diff.
2. **Decompose** — Checkpoints, flows, data, honest limits. Break down until nothing important is hand-waved. If unclear, read canonical docs first.
3. **Blueprint** — Which doc owns this? (`LIVIA-STATUS.md`, program doc, screen card, `AGENTS.md` cascade). **Update the plan if wrong; then build.**
4. **Trade scope** — Declare hat (`livia-session-hub`). Your branch must fit the main plan; cite the program doc in closeout.

## Build order (inside-out)

```text
lib/policy → DB/schema → API + services/jobs → pnpm codegen → artifacts/* (thin) → demo/E2E
```

Never fix one surface when the flow is shared — see `livia-surfaces-cascade.mdc`.

## Per trade (agent/session)

| Trade | Owns | Must verify |
|-------|------|-------------|
| Architect (cpo) | Intent, checkpoints, UX contract | Matches north-star / screen card |
| Structural (cto) | Policy, API, migrations, jobs | `typecheck`, cascade gates |
| Electrician | Integrations, auth, webhooks | Env truth, no fake “Connect” |
| Plumber | Tenant state, onboarding lifecycle | Resume + go-live gates |
| Painter | Dashboard/mobile/marketing UI | Parity or documented handoff |
| Inspector | E2E, UAT, readiness | Real user path, not happy-path only |

## Definition of done (a room, not a tile)

- [ ] Policy or program doc updated if behaviour changed
- [ ] API/OpenAPI + `pnpm codegen` if contract changed
- [ ] Sibling surfaces checked (web ↔ mobile ↔ `/b` ↔ demo)
- [ ] `pnpm run typecheck`; relevant E2E or founder path noted
- [ ] Honest limits in UI when automation is not live

## When user says “build X”

Default: short breakdown (intent → checkpoints → files → order) **then** implement.  
Exception: explicit “hotfix only” — still note cascade risk in closeout.

